Chain of Responsibility:- it lets you pass a request through a chain of handlers.

Each handler:

Decides to handle it or passes to next handler

- no giant if-else
- no tight coupling
- clean processing pipeline

this is Exactly how:
- HTTP middleware works
- Authentication chains work
- Validation pipelines work
- Logging + rate limiting + tracing layers work

we will build mini request pipeline:
 Logging -> Authentication -> Rate Limiting -> Final Handler

Project structure : -

    middleware-chain/
    │
    ├── go.mod
    ├── main.go
    │
    └── middleware/
        ├── handler.go
        ├── logging.go
        ├── auth.go
        ├── rate_limit.go
        └── final.go


How It Works ->

    If request = "valid-request":

    Logging
    → Authentication
    → Authorization
    → Business Logic


    If request = "invalid":

    Logging
    → Authentication ❌
    (stops here)